FoodBridge – Smart Surplus Food Redistribution System
1️⃣ Project Title

FoodBridge: Smart Surplus Food Redistribution System Using AI

Tagline:
“Bridging Surplus Food to Those in Need.”

2️⃣ Project Objective

The objective of FoodBridge is to reduce food waste by creating a digital platform that connects:

Restaurants

Caterers

with:

NGOs

Food banks

Volunteers

This system ensures surplus food is distributed efficiently to people in need.

3️⃣ Problem Statement

Every day large amounts of food are wasted in restaurants, events, and hotels, while many people suffer from hunger.

Current challenges include:

No real-time platform for food donation

Lack of coordination between donors and NGOs

Food spoilage due to delayed pickup

No tracking system for food redistribution

4️⃣ Proposed Solution

FoodBridge provides a smart platform that:

Allows donors to upload surplus food

Uses AI to predict food surplus

Automatically matches food with nearest NGOs

Sends real-time notifications to volunteers

Tracks distribution using a dashboard

5️⃣ System Architecture
4
Main Components

1️⃣ Food Sources
Restaurants, hotels, caterers

2️⃣ FoodBridge Platform
Central system managing donations

3️⃣ AI Prediction Engine
Predicts surplus food quantity

4️⃣ Matching Engine
Finds nearest NGO or shelter

5️⃣ Notification System
Alerts volunteers and NGOs

6️⃣ Impact Dashboard
Displays analytics and impact metrics

6️⃣ User Roles
User	Function
Donor	Upload surplus food
NGO	Accept food donations
Volunteer	Pick up and deliver food
Admin	Manage platform
